						<summary>

						<p>Mutilated slab kept in the shrine of Āñjanēya.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The mutilated and undated inscription can be assigned to 17th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Mention the god Ahōbalēśvara and Hanumantha at Chinttakuṇta.</p>						

